<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Valley Ridge</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Flanked by the Bow River on the North and the Trans-Canada Highway to the south, the neighborhood has been developed on the former site of the Happy Valley Campground that was shut down in the 1980s.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">The charming community in Valley Ridge majorly comprises of detached single family homes that are typically available at an average price of $640,000. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Alternatively, there are also a number of estate homes and apartments to cater to the varying tastes of homebuyers and investors alike. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Apart from its close proximity to a bunch of shopping centres and other essential public amenities, Valley Ridge real estate also houses the Fire Station 35 to ensure the peace of mind of its inhabitants. </p>
        </div>
